The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 December is 10,021 (1,159.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 December, there were 539 new confirmed cases (62.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 November, there were 533 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (6 extra cases).
